        "text": "We had pictures taken for our anniversary and it was so worth it!! Ryan was so friendly, patient, chill, and funny. It was nice to chat with him, he was a great conversationalist trying to get to know us and letting us get to know him a bit, and he made us laugh a lot!!  It really just felt like hanging out with a new friend.\n\nHe had great ideas throughout the session! It was SO RIDICULOUSLY WINDY but he made it work by helping us figure out placement/poses and timing to work with the wind.\n\nNot only do we have incredible pictures that we’ll cherish forever but he is also a cool dude and we had fun spending time with him. It was a blast and we hope to work with him again in the future when we visit!!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2025-08",
        "text": "Ryan is a fantastic photographer and an even better human! He photographed our mountain elopement and has such a fantastic way of capturing moments when you don't even know he's there. We couldn't be happier with the photos that he took - he got all of the shots we were hoping for and more. 10/10 recommend Ryan if you want someone to not just take some pictures of your elopement but really tell the story of the day."
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2026-05",
        "text": "We hired Ryan to capture photos at a graduation party at a local park. He did a fantastic job! The photos turned out great! They really capture the joy of the day and moment. He was also very fun and easy to work with. He did a great job putting everyone at ease especially the kids and getting the best possible shots from them. He took care and time to get a variety of poses and combinations with our family and friends. I'd highly recommend working with him and would hire him again!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2026-01",
        "text": "Ryan made our family photo shoot such a memorable time! I’m so thankful he was willing to fit us in during the hectic holiday week. Ryan encouraged us to be ourselves. We laughed and played and enjoyed one another. Most family photo shoots have been stressful and we couldn’t wait to be done — but the time we spent getting these pictures taken was one of the highlights of our few days together. The photos are great! I’m thankful to have high  resolution photos for having prints made and also smaller files that can be shared with family and friends online. I’d highly recommend Ryan to anyone wanting to capture their family “on film”.!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2025-07",
        "text": "We had a wonderful experience with Ryan, capturing three families together in the beautiful mountains near Colorado Springs. From first contact to final delivery of photos Ryan communicated promptly, kindly, and with attention to detail. We  booked the shoot from California ahead of our vacation in Colorado, and Ryan delivered ideas for location with exactly the kind of detail and consideration that helped us pick the best place for our group. During our hour together he was personal- learning nearly everyone’s name and directing with calm command. He was patient and unruffled by the natural chaos of 13 people, including young kids, as we posed and played around our chosen location. He came prepared with ideas for shots to capture our family, and also he adapted ideas in the moment that were brilliant. He took both posed and candid shots, managing to take a picture of the whole group and then zoom in to capture the details of hands held, a single smiling face, the moment someone whispered to someone else. The pictures are treasures! They beautifully show our family enjoying ourselves together and I can’t wait to put them up on the wall! Thank you, Ryan!"
      }
